            <title>[LU-4096] Do not allocate large buffer for readdir rpc in case of a small directory</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-4096</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Notes from Oleg:&lt;br/&gt;
Sincewe know the directory size at readdir time, we can estimate if we actually need a large buffer for readdir or not. This is not certain, but a good guess. additionally we can check mtime and if it&apos;s very recent, we might want to allow a slightly bigger buffer still to accounf for the possible directory growth&quot;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
